HEADWORD: Golding
<hw>Gold"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <ety>[From the golden color of
the blossoms.]</ety> <def>A conspicuous yellow flower, commonly the corn
marigold (<spn>Chrysanthemum segetum</spn>).</def> <altsp>[This word is
variously corrupted into <asp>gouland</asp>, <asp>gools</asp>,
<asp>gowan</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goldless</ent>⟦br⟧
